# Tab Bar Bottom Clearance

The app uses a custom floating tab bar (`CustomTabBar` in `app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`) that is `position: 'absolute'` at the bottom of the screen. It is approximately 90-100px tall including safe area insets.

**Every scrollable content area inside a tab screen must use `theme.spacing.tabBarClearance` (100px) as its bottom padding** so content is never hidden behind the tab bar.

## How to apply

For `FlatList`, set it on `contentContainerStyle`:

```tsx
<FlatList
  contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: theme.spacing.tabBarClearance }}
  ...
/>
```

For `ScrollView`, set it on `contentContainerStyle`:

```tsx
<ScrollView
  contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: theme.spacing.tabBarClearance }}
  ...
/>
```

## Common mistakes

- Using `theme.spacing.xxl` (48px) -- this is NOT enough clearance
- Using a magic number like `paddingBottom: 100` instead of the token
- Forgetting bottom padding entirely on a new tab screen
- Adding `marginBottom` to the last item instead of `paddingBottom` on the scroll container
